methods.name: _getFontStyles

Reads the computed font styles (font family name and font size) from the targeted
element and returns an object with the details.

methods.name: _truncateBreadcrumbs
methods.description:
Iterates over a list of items and determines which will fit into the
available width and which will not.

If any items do not fit, backtracks and reduces the available width to
ensure an overflowed icon will also fit.

Call when an item is interacted with by the user. The favorited cop will

methods.name: flushFavoritedChanges
methods.description:
Call this method when the state of `favorited` should be reconciled with
any outstanding changes that need to be made. Outstanding changes are
the "temporary" list of changes we need to make that haven't taken
effect.

elements.description:
### Usage

    <px-context-browser-trigger trigger={{openTrigger}}></px-context-browser-trigger>
    <px-context-browser open-trigger="[[openTrigger]]" items='[{"label":"Home","id":"home"},{"label":"Alerts","id":"alerts"},{"label":"Assets","id":"assets"}]'></px-context-browser>

### Styling
The following custom properties are available for styling.

Custom property | Description
:----------------|:-------------
`--px-context-browser-header-background-color` | Background color of the header
`--px-context-browser-header-border-color` | Bottom border color of the header
`--px-context-browser-header-text-color` | Text color of the header
`--px-context-browser-item-text-color` | Text color of the items
`--px-context-browser-item-background-color--hover` | Background color of the items on hover
`--px-context-browser-item-background-color--selected` | Background color of the item when selected
`--px-context-browser-item-text-color--selected` | Text color of the item when selected
`--px-context-browser-icon-stroke` | Color of the icon stroke
`--px-context-browser-icon-stroke--item-selected` | Color of the icon when the item is selected
`--px-context-browser-panel-border-color` | Border color of the panel
`--px-context-browser-panel-background-color` | Background color of the panel
`--px-context-browser-panel-width` | Width of the panel
`--px-context-browser-loading-background-color` | The background color of the loading bar
`--px-context-browser-loading-foreground-color` | The foreground color of the loading bar
`--px-context-browser-trigger-height` | The height of the trigger
`--px-context-browser-trigger-width` | The width of the trigger
`--px-context-browser-trigger-hover-background` | The background color of the trigger on hover
`--px-context-browser-trigger-icon-color` | The icon color of the trigger

properties.name: items
properties.description:
An array of objects that will be used to build the nav. Top-level items
can optionally have one level of children beneath them, turning the
top-level item into a dropdown group.

Selecting an item automatically selects its parent if it has one.
For the navigation, top-level items with children cannot be selected
directly - instead, users can select a child item and its parent will
also be marked as selected (and set as the `selectedItemParent`).

All items should have at least the following properties:

- {String} id - A unique string that identifies the item. Should only
contain valid ASCII characters. It's recommended to only use URI-safe
characters to allow for easy binding to the URL. Examples: 'home' or 'alerts'
- {String} label - A short, human-readable text label for the item.

The following optional properties can be used:

- {Array} children - An array of subitem objects that are children of
the item. Each child item should also have an `id` and `label`, and
may have its own child items.
- {Boolean=false} isTerminal - If `true` the item cannot have any children.
Terminal items can only be selected, not activated (navigated into).
Items with children should not be marked as terminal.
- {Boolean=false} isExhausted - If `true` the item does not have any
additional children available to load from a remote data source.
- {Boolean=true} isSelectable - If `false` the item can only be activated
(navigated into) to view its children, not selected.

The following is an example of a list of valid nav items:

    [
      { "label" : "Home",   "id" : "home" },
      { "label" : "Alerts", "id" : "alerts" },
      { "label" : "Assets", "id" : "assets", "children": [
        { "label" : "Asset #1", "id" : "a1" },
        { "label" : "Asset #2", "id" : "a2" }
      ] }
    ]

The item property names can be changed, e.g. to choose a different item
property to serve as a unique ID. See the `keys` property for details.

properties.name: keys
properties.description:
Changes the item properties (keys) that will be used internally to find
each item's unique ID, label, and child list.

Use this property if you already have a predefined data schema for your
application and want to customize this component to match your schema.
Otherwise, it's recommended to leave the defaults.

The following properties can be set:

- id: [default='id'] a unique ID for the item
- label: [default='label'] a human-readable label
- children: [default='children'] an array of child items

If you want to configure any keys, you must set all the keys. If any
of the keys are not defined, the navigation will fail.

For example, the schema could be changed to the following:

    {
      "id" : "assetId",
      "label" : "assetName",
      "children" : "subAssets"
    }

properties.name: selected
properties.description:
A reference to the currently selected item. Use this property to set the
selected item directly. The object passed to this property must be a
direct reference to one of the `items` objects. Changing this property
will automatically update the `selectedRoute`.

See `selectedRoute` for an alternative way to select items.

properties.name: selectedRoute
properties.description:
The route to the selected item as an array of strings. Use this property
to set the selected item by route, or to bind to updates when the
selected item is changed. Changing this property will automatically
update the `selected` item.

The route array starts at the top of the graph and ends with the selected
item. Each route entry is a string that corresponds to the unique ID
of an item. The item property that this unique ID will be taken from can be
configured with the `key` property. By default, it will be `item.id`.


For example, given the following graph:

    [
      {
        "label" : "Dashboards",
        "id" : "dash",
        "children" : [
          { "label" : "Truck Statuses", "id" : "trucks" },
          { "label" : "Generator Alerts", "id" : "generators" }
        ]
      },
    ]

To select the "Truck Statuses" page, set the route array to:

    ["dash", "trucks"]

If the user then selects the "Generator Alerts" item, the route array
would be replaced with a new array with the following entries:

    ["dash", "generators"]

properties.name: selectedMeta
properties.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the selected item.

SINGLE-SELECT MODE: An object with the following information about
the selected item (if no selected item, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the selected item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the selected item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the selected item. It
the selected item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the selected item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the selected item (see `selectedRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the selected item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the selected item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the selected item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the selected item
if it has no children.

MUTLI-SELECT MODE: An array of objects with metadata about each
selected item. Each object will be contain the same values as above.
If no items are selected, all values will be null.

properties.name: activeMeta
properties.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the active item.

SINGLE-ACTIVE MODE: An object with the following information about
the active item (if no active item, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the active item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the active item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the active item. If
the active item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the active item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the active item (see `activeRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the active item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the active item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the active item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the active item
if it has no children.

MULTI-ACTIVE MODE: An array of objects with metadata about each
active item. Each object will contain the same values as above.
If no items are active, all values will be null.

properties.name: favorited
properties.description:
A reference to the favorited items. Use this property to set the
favorited items directly. The objects passed to this property must be a
direct reference to one or more of the `items` objects. Changing this property
will automatically update the `favoritedRoute`.

See `favoritedRoute` for an alternative way to favorite items.

properties.name: favoritedRoute
properties.description:
The route to the favorited item as an array of strings. Use this property
to set the favorited item by route, or to bind to updates when the
favorited item is changed. Changing this property will automatically
update the `favorited` item.

The route array starts at the top of the graph and ends with the favorited
item. Each route entry is a string that corresponds to the unique ID
of an item. The item property that this unique ID will be taken from can be
configured with the `key` property. By default, it will be `item.id`.


For example, given the following graph:

    [
      {
        "label" : "Dashboards",
        "id" : "dash",
        "children" : [
          { "label" : "Truck Statuses", "id" : "trucks" },
          { "label" : "Generator Alerts", "id" : "generators" }
        ]
      },
    ]

To favorite the "Truck Statuses" page, set the route array to:

    ["dash", "trucks"]

If the user then favorites the "Generator Alerts" item, the route array
would be replaced with a new array with the following entries:

    ["dash", "generators"]

properties.name: favoritedMeta
properties.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the favorited item.

An array of objects with metadata about each favorited item. Each
object will contain the following information about the favorited item
(if no items are favorited, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the favorited item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the favorited item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the favorited item. It
the favorited item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the favorited item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the favorited item (see `favoritedRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the favorited item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the favorited item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the favorited item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the favorited item
if it has no children.

properties.name: multiFavorite
properties.description: set multiFavorite to true at the start and make it non-configurable.

properties.name: _parentResizable
properties.description: The closest ancestor element that implements `IronResizableBehavior`.

properties.name: _notifyingDescendant
properties.description:
True if this element is currently notifying its descendant elements of
resize.

properties.name: __localizationCache
properties.description:
Internal singleton cache. This is the private implementation of the
behaviour; don't interact with it directly.

properties.name: language
properties.description:
A valid IETF language tag as a string that `app-localize-behavior` will
use to localize this component.

See https://github.com/PolymerElements/app-localize-behavior for API
documentation and more information.

properties.name: resources
properties.description:
Library object of hardcoded strings used in this application.
Used by `app-localize-behavior` in conjunction with `language`.
properties.defaultValue: {"en":{"You don't have any favorites yet.":"You don't have any favorites yet.","To favorite a context, click on the star while viewing a context in the context browser.":"To favorite a context, click on the star while viewing a context in the context browser.","Filter":"Filter"}}

properties.name: formats
useKeyIfMissing
properties.description:
Use the key for localization if value for that language is missing.
Should always be true for Predix components.

properties.name: localize
properties.description:
Translates a string to the current `language`. Any parameters to the
string should be passed in order, as follows:
`localize(stringKey, param1Name, param1Value, param2Name, param2Value)`

properties.name: bubbleEvent
properties.description: If true, will bubble up the event to the parents

properties.name: showFavorited
properties.description:
Enable to show a star icon next to each item. The user can tap the star
to add that item to their favorited list.

properties.name: showArrow
properties.description:
Enable to show an arrow when the user hovers over an item that has
children and can be activated.

properties.name: showFilter
properties.description:
Enable to show a filter input that filters the visible column. Changes
to the filter text are notified out through the `filter` property.

properties.name: filter
properties.description:
User-supplied filter text to filter items in the context browser.
The string will be lowercased and compared to the label of each item
in the currently visible column.

properties.name: favoritedFilter
properties.description:
User-supplied filter text to filter items in the favorited panel.
The string will be lowercased and compared to the label of each item
in the favorited panel.

properties.name: loadingTimeout
properties.description:
When an item is activated and it has no children, the context browser
shows a loading animation and fires an event to request children to
show (see `px-app-asset-children-requested`). If no new children are
added before this timeout, the browser will show the last active item.

Set a time in milliseconds. Set to `0` to wait forever. Default to 5
seconds (5000 milliseconds).

properties.name: loading
properties.description:
Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is trying to
load new children.

properties.name: openTrigger
properties.description:
Bind to a `<px-context-browser-trigger>` element. A tap on the trigger
will open the context browser.

properties.name: favoritedTrigger
properties.description:
Bind to a `<px-context-browser-trigger>` element. A tap on the favorited
trigger will open a list of favorited items in the context browser.

properties.name: opened
properties.description: If `true` the context browser is opened to the navigation view.

properties.name: favoritedOpened
properties.description: If `true` the context browser is opened to the favorited view.

properties.name: keepOpen
properties.description:
If `true` the context browser will remain opened even after a context is selected.
The only way to dismiss the context browser will be clicking the trigger again,
or using the ESC key.

properties.name: collapseAt
properties.description:
The width below which the context browser will collapse into a mobile
friendly menu that slides up from the bottom of the page. Use a number
(e.g. `450`) which will be converted to a pixel value (e.g. '450px').

If no value is provided, the context browser will not collapse
automatically. The collapsed attribute can also be used to manually
collapse and un-collapse the context browser.

properties.name: collapsed
properties.description: Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is collapsed.

properties.name: favoritedSyncFailed
properties.description:
Set to true if your app fails to sync the user's favorited list to the
server. Shows a notification bar informing the user that the sync
failed and allows them to tap an icon to attempt to sync the favorited
list again. Listen for the NAME_OF_EVENT event to receive a
notification when the user requests a new sync attempt.

properties.name: favoritedSyncing
properties.description:
Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is trying to
sync its favorited items.

properties.name: __this
properties.description: Reference to this context browser instance, for data-binding.

methods.name: addChildren
methods.description:
Adds a child or children to the requested node. Pass a single object
to add one child, or an array of objects to add multiple children.

The `node` should be a direct reference to one of the objects already
in the asset graph (e.g. one of the `items` objects or another node
added through the `addChildren` API). To remove children from the root
of the graph, call with `node` as null.

methods.name: removeChildren
methods.description:
Removes a child or children from the requested node. Pass `children` a
single object to remove one child, an array of objects to remove multiple
children, or null to remove all children.

The `node` should be a direct reference to one of the objects already
in the asset graph (e.g. one of the `items` objects or another node
added through the `addChildren` API). To add children to the root
of the graph, call with `node` as null.

methods.name: select
methods.description:
Selects an item. Call with an object that is a direct reference to one
of the `items` objects.

If multi-select mode is enabled, call with an object to select a single
item or an array of objects to select multiple items.

An optional source of the change can be provided as a string.

methods.name: deselect
methods.description:
Deselects an item. Call with a direct reference to the selected item
or with `null` to deselect whatever is selected.

If multi-select mode is enabled, call with a direct reference to one of
the selected items to deselect it, or an array of selected items to
deselect multiple, or `null` to deselect all items.

methods.name: _assetSelectedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _assetDeselectedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _selectedRouteChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `selectedRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `selected` observer triggering `selectedRoute` observer.

methods.name: _selectedChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `selectedRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `selected` observer triggering `selectedRoute` observer.

methods.name: activate
methods.description:
Activates an item. Call with an object that is a direct reference to one
of the `items` objects.

If multi-activate mode is enabled, call with an object to activate a single
item or an array of objects to activate multiple items.

An optional source of the change can be provided as a string.

methods.name: deactivate
methods.description:
Deactivates an item. Call with a direct reference to the active item
or with `null` to deactivate whatever is active.

If multi-activate mode is enabled, call with a direct reference to one of
the active items to deactivate it, or an array of active items to
deactivate multiple, or `null` to deactivate all items.

methods.name: _assetActivatedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _assetDeactivatedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _activeRouteChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `activeRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `active` observer triggering `activeRoute` observer.

methods.name: _activeChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `activeRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `active` observer triggering `activeRoute` observer.

methods.name: favorite
methods.description:
Call with an object that is a direct reference to one of the `items`
objects to favorite a single item, or with an array of objects to favorite
multiple items.

An optional source of the change can be provided as a string.

methods.name: defavorite
methods.description:
Defavorites one or more items. Call with a direct reference to one of
the favorited items to defavorite it, or an array of favorited items to
defavorite multiple, or `null` to defavorite all items.

methods.name: _assetFavoritedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _assetDefavoritedByEvent
methods.description: The event `detail.item` should be a reference to an item in the asset graph.

methods.name: _favoritedRouteChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `favoritedRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `favorited` observer triggering `favoritedRoute` observer.

methods.name: _favoritedChanged
methods.description:
Should only sync changes to `favoritedRoute` when necessary to avoid
infinite loop of `favorited` observer triggering `favoritedRoute` observer.

methods.name: notifyResize
methods.description:
Can be called to manually notify a resizable and its descendant
resizables of a resize change.

methods.name: assignParentResizable
methods.description:
Used to assign the closest resizable ancestor to this resizable
if the ancestor detects a request for notifications.

methods.name: stopResizeNotificationsFor
methods.description:
Used to remove a resizable descendant from the list of descendants
that should be notified of a resize change.

methods.description:
This method can be overridden to filter nested elements that should or
should not be notified by the current element. Return true if an element
should be notified, or false if it should not be notified.

params.name: element
params.description:
A candidate descendant element that
implements `IronResizableBehavior`.

return.desc: True if the `element` should be notified of resize.

methods.name: __computeLocalize
methods.description: Returns a computed `localize` method, based on the current `language`.

methods.name: _updateCancelFilterFocus
methods.description:
When the user is navigating the collapsed browser, if they press on the
header a little bit too long and the filter is active, when the filter
slides up it will sometimes be activated and open the keyboard. To
prevent this, we blur the filter if it becomes focused less than 200ms
after we navigate to the root.

methods.name: cancelLoading
methods.description:
Cancels the current child loading event, if one is in progress. Changes
the active browser view to the previously loading item's parent.

methods.name: clearFilter
methods.description: Clears the active filter text.

methods.name: _handleBrowserCanceled
methods.description:
If the user clicked on the open or the favorited trigger, we'll let the
trigger close the dropdown on its own.

methods.name: _handleBrowserOpened
methods.description: If the browser is opened before the reset active task runs, cancel it.

methods.name: _handleBrowserClosed
methods.description:
After 5 seconds, reset the active to the parent of the selected item,
or to the root if no item is selected.

methods.name: _getItemProp
methods.description:
Fetches an item's property at the configured key. Used to dynamically
fetch the item's label, icon, children, etc. based on the configured
`keys` for the app.

        "id" : "dash",
        "children" : [
          { "label" : "Truck Statuses", "id" : "trucks" },
          { "label" : "Generator Alerts", "id" : "generators" }
        ]
      },
    ]

To select the "Truck Statuses" page, set the route array to:

    ["dash", "trucks"]

If the user then selects the "Generator Alerts" item, the route array
would be replaced with a new array with the following entries:

    ["dash", "generators"]

attributes.name: selected-meta
attributes.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the selected item.

SINGLE-SELECT MODE: An object with the following information about
the selected item (if no selected item, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the selected item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the selected item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the selected item. It
the selected item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the selected item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the selected item (see `selectedRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the selected item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the selected item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the selected item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the selected item
if it has no children.

MUTLI-SELECT MODE: An array of objects with metadata about each
selected item. Each object will be contain the same values as above.
If no items are selected, all values will be null.

attributes.name: active-meta
attributes.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the active item.

SINGLE-ACTIVE MODE: An object with the following information about
the active item (if no active item, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the active item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the active item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the active item. If
the active item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the active item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the active item (see `activeRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the active item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the active item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the active item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the active item
if it has no children.

MULTI-ACTIVE MODE: An array of objects with metadata about each
active item. Each object will contain the same values as above.
If no items are active, all values will be null.

attributes.name: favorited
attributes.description:
A reference to the favorited items. Use this property to set the
favorited items directly. The objects passed to this property must be a
direct reference to one or more of the `items` objects. Changing this property
will automatically update the `favoritedRoute`.

See `favoritedRoute` for an alternative way to favorite items.

attributes.name: favorited-route
attributes.description:
The route to the favorited item as an array of strings. Use this property
to set the favorited item by route, or to bind to updates when the
favorited item is changed. Changing this property will automatically
update the `favorited` item.

The route array starts at the top of the graph and ends with the favorited
item. Each route entry is a string that corresponds to the unique ID
of an item. The item property that this unique ID will be taken from can be
configured with the `key` property. By default, it will be `item.id`.


For example, given the following graph:

    [
      {
        "label" : "Dashboards",
        "id" : "dash",
        "children" : [
          { "label" : "Truck Statuses", "id" : "trucks" },
          { "label" : "Generator Alerts", "id" : "generators" }
        ]
      },
    ]

To favorite the "Truck Statuses" page, set the route array to:

    ["dash", "trucks"]

If the user then favorites the "Generator Alerts" item, the route array
would be replaced with a new array with the following entries:

    ["dash", "generators"]

attributes.name: favorited-meta
attributes.description:
[Read-only] Helpful metadata about the favorited item.

An array of objects with metadata about each favorited item. Each
object will contain the following information about the favorited item
(if no items are favorited, all values will be null):

- {Object} `item`: Reference to the favorited item
- {Array} `path`: The path to the favorited item as an array. Begins with
the top-most item in the graph and ends with the favorited item. It
the favorited item is at the top of the graph, the array will include
only the favorited item.
- {Array} `route`: Route to the favorited item (see `favoritedRoute`
for more information on how this is created)
- {Object} `parent`: Reference to the favorited item's parent,
or `null` if it has no parent
- {Array} `children`: Reference to the favorited item's children,
or empty array if it has no children
- {Array} `siblings`: Reference to the favorited item's siblings (e.g.
the children of its parent) or an array with only the favorited item
if it has no children.

attributes.name: language
attributes.description:
A valid IETF language tag as a string that `app-localize-behavior` will
use to localize this component.

See https://github.com/PolymerElements/app-localize-behavior for API
documentation and more information.

attributes.name: resources
attributes.description:
Library object of hardcoded strings used in this application.
Used by `app-localize-behavior` in conjunction with `language`.

attributes.name: formats
use-key-if-missing
attributes.description:
Use the key for localization if value for that language is missing.
Should always be true for Predix components.

attributes.name: localize
attributes.description:
Translates a string to the current `language`. Any parameters to the
string should be passed in order, as follows:
`localize(stringKey, param1Name, param1Value, param2Name, param2Value)`

attributes.name: bubble-event
attributes.description: If true, will bubble up the event to the parents

attributes.name: show-favorited
attributes.description:
Enable to show a star icon next to each item. The user can tap the star
to add that item to their favorited list.

attributes.name: show-arrow
attributes.description:
Enable to show an arrow when the user hovers over an item that has
children and can be activated.

attributes.name: show-filter
attributes.description:
Enable to show a filter input that filters the visible column. Changes
to the filter text are notified out through the `filter` property.

attributes.name: filter
attributes.description:
User-supplied filter text to filter items in the context browser.
The string will be lowercased and compared to the label of each item
in the currently visible column.

attributes.name: favorited-filter
attributes.description:
User-supplied filter text to filter items in the favorited panel.
The string will be lowercased and compared to the label of each item
in the favorited panel.

attributes.name: loading-timeout
attributes.description:
When an item is activated and it has no children, the context browser
shows a loading animation and fires an event to request children to
show (see `px-app-asset-children-requested`). If no new children are
added before this timeout, the browser will show the last active item.

Set a time in milliseconds. Set to `0` to wait forever. Default to 5
seconds (5000 milliseconds).

attributes.name: loading
attributes.description:
Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is trying to
load new children.

attributes.name: open-trigger
attributes.description:
Bind to a `<px-context-browser-trigger>` element. A tap on the trigger
will open the context browser.

attributes.name: favorited-trigger
attributes.description:
Bind to a `<px-context-browser-trigger>` element. A tap on the favorited
trigger will open a list of favorited items in the context browser.

attributes.name: opened
attributes.description: If `true` the context browser is opened to the navigation view.

attributes.name: favorited-opened
attributes.description: If `true` the context browser is opened to the favorited view.

attributes.name: keep-open
attributes.description:
If `true` the context browser will remain opened even after a context is selected.
The only way to dismiss the context browser will be clicking the trigger again,
or using the ESC key.

attributes.name: collapse-at
attributes.description:
The width below which the context browser will collapse into a mobile
friendly menu that slides up from the bottom of the page. Use a number
(e.g. `450`) which will be converted to a pixel value (e.g. '450px').

If no value is provided, the context browser will not collapse
automatically. The collapsed attribute can also be used to manually
collapse and un-collapse the context browser.

attributes.name: collapsed
attributes.description: Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is collapsed.

attributes.name: favorited-sync-failed
attributes.description:
Set to true if your app fails to sync the user's favorited list to the
server. Shows a notification bar informing the user that the sync
failed and allows them to tap an icon to attempt to sync the favorited
list again. Listen for the NAME_OF_EVENT event to receive a
notification when the user requests a new sync attempt.

attributes.name: favorited-syncing
attributes.description:
Watch for changes to determine if the context browser is trying to
sync its favorited items.
